# Git Commit Format

Always use this exact format for every git commit:

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
type: short title here

- detail one
- detail two
- detail three
EOF
)"
```

## Commit Types

| type | when to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | new feature |
| `fix` | bug fix |
| `init` | first commit |
| `style` | CSS/UI only changes |
| `refactor` | code improvement, no new feature |
| `chore` | config or dependency changes |

## Rules

- Title must be short and descriptive (max 72 chars)
- Always include at least 2 bullet points describing what changed
- Never use `git commit -m "message"` single-line format
- NEVER add Co-authored-by lines or any co-author attribution — ever
